Source: bearssl
Section: net
Priority: optional
Maintainer: multiplexd <multi@in-addr.xyz>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 10), dh-exec (>= 0.23), quilt
Standards-Version: 3.9.8
Homepage: https://www.bearssl.org

Package: libbearssl-bin
Architecture: any
Section: net
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: A small and portable implementation of the SSL/TLS protocol written in C (testing utilities)
 BearSSL is an implementation of the SSL/TLS protocol (RFC 5246) written
 in C. It aims to be correct, secure, small, portable, and extensible. It
 is currently considered beta-quality software.
 .
 This package contains the BearSSL testing utilities.

